text: What I really loved about this film was that while they teased her about how she looks, they didn't exclusively include fat jokes. For example, there's a scene where she gets into a small car, but they don't make the car lean heavily on her side. When she's running after villains, they don't make her run out of breathe. When in a restaurant, they don't joke about the amount she eats. She isn't embarrassing around men and she isn't intimidated by the seemingly prettier woman. Her character comes into her own, not by dressing up or being seen as desirable by men, but by showing her colleagues the kind of agent she is and has always been - a kick ass one.

text: I saw this on Sunday and thought it was great. I'm sure Anita Sarkeesian would find a way to be offended by it, but I don't remember a single joke targeting McCarthy's weight or appearance  (outside of the suggestion that she looked like a "cat lady," which would have worked just as well with Kristen Wiig), and it was chock full of strong female characters who could be both goofy and assertive. There was some physical comedy, but the script was pretty smartly written. All of you "this fat pig isn't funny" folks need to address your own double standard (setting aside the fact that McCarthy is not a bad looking woman, I doubt that any of you have such a viscerally hateful reaction to Chris Farley) and all of you "she deserves better" folks need to get off your high horses.

text: I'm so glad I managed to avoid the trailer before seeing it. So many funny parts in this trailer caught me by surprise, ESPECIALLY when Jude Law sneezes and accidently busts a cap in the guys head. I was laughing so much.  Jason Statham too was a real funny jackass in this. Trying to  brag about all the impossible shit he's done. So much of this movie was great. Had NO IDEA a month later I would be an extra in Paul Feig's and Melissa McCarthy's next collaboration Ghostbusters III. So the Summer started with this hilarious movie and i liked both of them as actor/director...then was lucky enough to be on set a few times fot GB III. I still can't tell whether it will be good or not, but with a tag-team like them, they SHOULD be able to make it funny (I was just too busy running from ghosts that weren't even there).
